    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;">(It was just another day in the clubroom as any. But there was one thing missing from the normal experience here - Sayori. She had always been there for me. I could see Monika working on a new poem. Even though I was 5 months pregnant, I felt a sense of worry. Just then, Yuri approached me.)<br/><br/>Yuri: &quot;Is everything okay, Natsuki?&quot;<br/><br/>(I turned towards her - the weight of my pregnancy obvious. Just then, Sayori entered the room.)<br/><br/>Sayori: &quot;Hey, guys! Sorry I&#x27;m late! I was getting stuff ready for Natsuki&#x27;s gender reveal.&quot;<br/><br/>(She had brought all the things needed for my gender reveal - pink and blue balloons and everything. However, she brough two black balloons with her - which puzzled me.)</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>Natsuki: "Uh, Sayori, why do you have black balloons? Are those part of the gender reveal too?"</p>
<p>Sayori: "Oh, um, those are just an extra surprise. You'll understand later!"</p>
<p>Yuri: "Interesting choice of colors, Sayori. I'm curious to see what you have planned."</p>
<p>Monika: "Well, I'm excited regardless. Let's get this gender reveal started!"</p>
<p>(Sayori began setting up the balloons and decorations while the rest of us gathered around, anticipation filling the room. Finally, everything was ready.)</p>
<p>Sayori: "Okay, Natsuki and... well, you'll see. Are you ready?"</p>
<p>Natsuki: "As ready as I'll ever be. Let's do this."</p>
<p>(Sayori handed me a pin and gestured towards the balloons, urging me to pop them. With a deep breath, I approached the balloons, unsure of what would happen next. I chose the blue balloon first, and as it popped, blue confetti showered down.)</p>
<p>Yuri: "It's a boy! Congratulations, Natsuki!"</p>
<p>Monika: "Oh, that's wonderful news! A baby boy!"</p>
<p>(Smiles and excitement filled the room as we celebrated the announcement. However, my curiosity about the black balloons still lingered.)</p>
<p>Natsuki: "Okay, Sayori, now that we know it's a boy, care to explain what those black balloons are for?"</p>
<p>Sayori: "Well, Natsuki, the black balloons represent a little surprise. You see, at your next doctor's appointment, ask them to keep the baby's gender a secret and write it down for me. Those black balloons will be released during the baby shower, revealing the true gender!"</p>
<p>Natsuki: "Oh, Sayori! That's such a creative idea! I love it!"</p>
<p>(Sayori's surprise continued to amaze me. It added an extra level of excitement and mystery to the whole experience.)</p>
<p>Yuri: "I must say, Sayori, you truly know how to keep things interesting. I can't wait for the baby shower now!"</p>
<p>Monika: "Indeed, Sayori. You always know how to make events memorable. Thank you for putting so much effort into this."</p>
<p>(Sayori blushed and smiled, clearly pleased with our reactions.)</p>
<p>Sayori: "You're all very welcome! I just want the best for Natsuki and her little one. Let's make this a celebration to remember!"</p>
<p>(We all nodded in agreement, grateful for the friendship and support we found within the club. With Sayori's surprises and our upcoming baby shower, the days ahead were sure to be filled with joy and anticipation.)</p></div>

